f:\,\mathbb{R}^{+}\rightarrow\mathbb{R},\, f\in C^{\infty}\left(\mathbb{R}^{+}\right)
f\left(n\right)>0\,\forall n\in\mathbb{N}
c>0
N>0
e\left(x\right):=e^{2\pi ix}
\forall k\in\left[1,\,2N\right]
\left|\underset{\underset{n_{1}+n_{2}=k}{n_{1},\, n_{2}\leq N}}{\sum}\left(f\left(n_{1}\right)f\left(n_{2}\right)\, e\left(c\left(n_{1}+n_{2}\right)\right)\right)\right|\leq\left|\underset{n_{1},\, n_{2}\leq N}{\sum}\left(f\left(n_{1}\right)f\left(n_{2}\right)\, e\left(c\left(n_{1}+n_{2}\right)\right)\right)\right|?
